import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

# URL of the vulnerability details on cvedetails.com
url = 'https://www.cvedetails.com/cve/CVE-2022-34877/'

# Send a GET request to retrieve the page content
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if the request was successful
if response.status_code == 200:
    # Parse the HTML content using BeautifulSoup
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser')
    
    # Extract the vulnerability details using CSS selectors
    name = soup.select_one('h1.CVEcache-id').text.strip()
    summary = soup.select_one('div.CVERTtilestatus_text').text.strip()
    cvss_score = soup.select_one('a[href^="/cvss"]').text.strip()
    publish_date = soup.select_one('td#param_published.string content span.weightValue').text.strip()
    
    print(f"Vulnerability Name: {name}")
    print(f"Summary: {summary}")
    print(f"CVSS Score: {cvss_score}")
    print(f"Publish Date: {publish_date}")
else:
    print("Failed to retrieve the page contents.")
